claim.claim-text:
1. A method of singulating embryos, comprising:
(a) providing a plurality of embryos in a fluid;
(b) sensing at least one of the plurality of embryos by a sensor;
(c) maintaining a substantially constant flow rate of embryos in a tube past the sensor;
(d) tracking the at least one of the plurality of embryos within the tube; and
(e) depositing the at least one of the plurality of embryos on a surface.
